Review: This one’s for the ladies, I think!

Maybe I have some character flaws, but I found this so incredibly boring that I started to fantasize about cleaning my apartment. These urges were so strong I left the theater early to go browse the Target two stories below and look at cleaning supplies while I waited for Oppenheimer to finish.
I don’t think I’ve seen something that was just straight up fun like this in a minute. 3 hours later and I’m still feeling fun.  I’m gonna watch it again rn

Movie: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call – New Orleans

Review: I do love a who dunnit where it’s absolutely impossible to figure it out as an audience member. Clues that mean absolutely nothing are crucial in these types of movies. I’m saying that as a lady who has watched every episode of Law and Order SVU twice, and therefore is good on picking up clues.
This was like an episode of Law and Order SVU without the cops but where everything is made right in the end
All I know is this movie has been on like 20 hours.

Movie: Tiny: The Life of Erin Blackwell

Review: Hard mids. My moms favorite movie of all time, or so she claims, but I know for a fact she has better taste than that. The color in this was so good. I need a reminder every once in a while that wallpaper is the epitome of class. However, story was boring and the reason that isn’t okay in this particular instance is that it’s a musical. It should be fun and easy to find yourself into. But it wasn’t, and the ending was sad and hollow, but not in a way that made me feel. Very whatever

This is a movie I’d imagine has an entirely different viewing experience for men and women. I can see how it’d be easy to find Layla to be a passive character, and her demeanor towards Billy is so odd, especially when you consider that you know nothing about her. My only question was, what didn’t she want to go home to? If that was answered then I could have understood her attitude. Beneath all that though, there’s this tenderness she…

Epic poggers! I do love a good cruise ship love story. Two charming people surrounded by the vast ocean with no distractions.  The ending was a little silly… but not bad. I’d just never wait 6 months to see somebody again if I really loved them.
Should be titled “I don’t understand women”
